{
  "texts": [
    "(B.4)Notice that the flip of vertex colour is accompanied by a flip of momentum in the kinematic structure in addition to the complex conjugation.",
    "We start by noticing that the total-energy singularities can only reside in monochromatic diagrams where the vertices are either all-black or all-white.",
    "This is simply a consequence of the factorised nature of the Wightman functions G ±∓ (η 1, η 2, k), i.e.",
    "any polychromatic diagram is necessarily disconnected in time at the internal line with opposite colours.",
    "In the wavefunction formalism language, they correspond to contributions from the factorised third term in the bulk-bulk propagator (1.7) together with sewing disconnected ρ n in (4.48)."
  ]
}